VTyagaraja aradhana on campus
p3
sVnews
p4
VSYED MUTHAHAR SAQAFThe students of the Department of Music, Seethalakshmi Ramaswami College, Tiruchi, paid homage to Sathguru Sri Tyagaraja during his 159th aradhana by rendering Pancharatna kirtanas at the college premises recently.The department has been organising music programmes periodically  to kindle the students' interest and enthusiasm and develop their skills.The students sang the Pancharatna kirtanas of  Tyagaraja.Sankari Krishnan,   a student of  violin maestro, Lalgudi G. Jayaraman, gave a concert.   She performed with perfect sruthi suddha, maintaining an intelligent balance all through the concert. Her sharp and crisp kalpanaswaras in the kritis "Vidajaladura'' in Janaranjani and "Bantureethi Kolu'' in Hamsanadam  were highly appreciated.She was accompanied by K. N. Sathiamoorthy on the violin, Koviladi R. Madhwaprasad on the mridangam and S. Rajaganesh on the kanjira.Bottom Template Starts
